      • onGetLibraryRoot

        @Nullable
public MediaLibraryService2.LibraryRoot onGetLibraryRoot(@NonNull
                                                                   MediaLibraryService2.MediaLibrarySession session,
                                                                   @NonNull
                                                                   MediaSession2.ControllerInfo controllerInfo,
                                                                   @Nullable
                                                                   Bundle extras)
        Called to get the root information for browsing by a particular client.

        The implementation should verify that the client package has permission to access browse media information before returning the root id; it should return null if the client is not allowed to access this information.

        Note: this callback may be called on the main thread, regardless of the callback executor.

        Parameters:
        session - the session for this event
        controllerInfo - information of the controller requesting access to browse media.
        extras - An optional bundle of service-specific arguments to send to the media library service when connecting and retrieving the root id for browsing, or null if none. The contents of this bundle may affect the information returned when browsing.
        Returns:
        The MediaLibraryService2.LibraryRoot for accessing this app's content or null.
        See Also:
        MediaLibraryService2.LibraryRoot.EXTRA_RECENT, MediaLibraryService2.LibraryRoot.EXTRA_OFFLINE, MediaLibraryService2.LibraryRoot.EXTRA_SUGGESTED, SessionCommand2.COMMAND_CODE_LIBRARY_GET_LIBRARY_ROOT

        Called to get children of given parent id. Return the children here for the browser.

        Return an empty list for no children, and return null for the error.

        Parameters:
        session - the session for this event
        parentId - parent id to get children
        page - number of page
        pageSize - size of the page
        extras - extra bundle
        Returns:
        list of children. Can be null.

      • onGetSearchResult

        @Nullable
public java.util.List<MediaItem2> onGetSearchResult(@NonNull
                                                              MediaLibraryService2.MediaLibrarySession session,
                                                              @NonNull
                                                              MediaSession2.ControllerInfo controllerInfo,
                                                              @NonNull
                                                              java.lang.String query,
                                                              int page,
                                                              int pageSize,
                                                              @Nullable
                                                              Bundle extras)
        Called to get the search result. Return search result here for the browser which has requested search previously.

        Return an empty list for no search result, and return null for the error.

        Parameters:
        session - the session for this event
        controllerInfo - Information of the controller requesting the search result.
        query - The search query which was previously sent through #onSearch(MediaLibrarySession, ControllerInfo, String, Bundle).
        page - page number. Starts from 1.
        pageSize - page size. Should be greater or equal to 1.
        extras - The bundle of service-specific arguments sent from the media browser.
        Returns:
        search result. null for error.
        See Also:
        SessionCommand2.COMMAND_CODE_LIBRARY_GET_SEARCH_RESULT

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
